Teachers lined up for their COVID-19 vaccine on Wednesday. But day one of the vaccine rollout wasn't without some glitches. eNCA's Heidi Giokos takes a look. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some teachers have finally received a shot in the arm. But day one of the vaccine rollout wasn't without some glitches. READ: Teacher vaccination programme kicks off One vaccination site in Gauteng had no doses while there was no water at another. Gauteng's Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi also got his shot. * eNCA's Heidi Giokos reports.